<!-- Introduction-->
  <sect1 id="introduction"> 
	 <title>Introduction</title> 
	 <para>The <application>&app;</application> application enables users with limited vision, or no vision, to use the GNOME Desktop and associated applications. 
		<application>&app;</application>  provides the following functionality:</para>
	 <variablelist><varlistentry><term>Screen reader</term><listitem><para>The screen reader enables non-visual access to standard applications in the GNOME Desktop, using speech and Braille output.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist><variablelist><varlistentry><term>Magnifier</term><listitem><para>The magnifier   provides automated focus tracking and fullscreen magnification to aid low-vision users.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist><para>For more information about <application>&app;</application>, visit the following website: <ulink url="http://www.baum.ro/gnopernicus.html">http://www.baum.ro/gnopernicus</ulink></para></sect1>

<!-- Getting Started-->
  <sect1 id="getting-started"> 
	 <title>Getting Started</title> 
	 <sect2 id="gnopernicus-start"><title>To Start Gnopernicus</title><para>
		You can start <application>&app;</application> in the following ways:</para>
	 <variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
		  <term>Applications menu</term>
		  <listitem>
			 
		  <para>Choose 
    		<menuchoice>
    		    <guisubmenu>Accessibility</guisubmenu>
		    
    		    <guimenuitem>Screen Reader and Magnifier</guimenuitem>
    		</menuchoice>. </para></listitem>
		</varlistentry>
	 <varlistentry>
		  <term>Command line</term>
		  <listitem>
			 <para>
				Execute the following command: 
				<command>gnopernicus</command>
			 </para><para>You can use the <option>-d</option>   option to specify default settings.</para>
		  </listitem>
		</varlistentry>
		</variablelist> 
	 </sect2>
<sect2 id="gnopernicus-started"><title>When You Start Gnopernicus</title><para>
		When you start <application>&app;</application>, the <guilabel>Gnopernicus</guilabel> menu window appears:
	 </para>
		<!-- ==== Figure ==== -->
		<figure id="mainwindow-fig">
		<title>&app; Menu Window</title>
		<screenshot>
		  <mediaobject>
		    <imageobject>
		      <imagedata fileref="figures/gnopernicus.png" format="PNG"/>
		    </imageobject>
		    <textobject>
		      <phrase>Shows Gnopernicus menu window. Contains launchers for Startup Mode, Preferences, Default Preferences, Minimize, Help, About, and Quit.</phrase>
		    </textobject>
		  </mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
		</figure>
		<!-- ==== End of Figure ==== -->

<para>The <guilabel>Gnopernicus</guilabel>  menu window contains the following items:</para>
	 
	  
  <variablelist><varlistentry><term>Startup Mode</term><listitem><para>The <guilabel>Startup Mode</guilabel> dialog enables you to choose the functionality that you want <application>&app;</application> to provide when you launch the application. You can also apply functionality changes while you are using the application.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>Preferences</term><listitem><para>You can adjust the settings for speech output, magnifier behavior, Braille output, Braille monitor, mouse behavior, and key mapping.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>Default Preferences</term><listitem><para>You can click on this item at any time to load the default settings for <application>&app;</application>.</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Minimize</term><listitem><para>You can click on this item to minimize the <guilabel>Gnopernicus</guilabel>  menu window.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>Help</term><listitem><para>You can click on this item to open the Help manual for <application>&app;</application>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>About</term><listitem><para>You can click on this item to read developer information about the <application>&app;</application> application.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>Quit</term><listitem><para>You can click on this item to exit <application>&app;</application> at any time.</para>  </listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="gnopernicus-usage"><title>Usage</title><para><application>&app;</application>  functions are mapped onto  keys on the  numeric keypad. Because the number of keys on the numeric keypad are limited, the functions are assigned in layers. Any  key can have multiple functions, depending on which layer is active.  You can use the assigned layers of the <application>&app;</application> numeric keypad to work with the different functional areas of the application. The numeric keypad codes are written as follows: Layer<emphasis>nn</emphasis>Key<emphasis>nn</emphasis>, where Layer<emphasis>nn</emphasis> represents the number of the keypad layer, and Key<emphasis>nn</emphasis> represents the key value. The following sections include some useful numeric keypad assigned actions. </para>

<para>You can modify the defined actions for the numeric keypad layers, and you can also assign a keystroke sequence to any key on your keyboard, using the following modifiers:
</para>
<itemizedlist>
	<listitem>
		<para>Control
		</para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
		<para>Alt
		</para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
		<para>Shift
		</para>
	</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<para>See <xref linkend="gnopernicus-layers"/> for more information about numeric keypad actions.</para>
<sect2 id="gnopernicus-layer-switch"><title>To Switch Between Numeric Keypad Layers</title>
<para>To switch between numeric keypad layers, perform the following actions: <orderedlist><listitem><para>Switch on the Num Lock.</para></listitem><listitem><para>Press the  <keycap>0</keycap> key on the  numeric keypad.</para></listitem><listitem><para>Press the key on the numeric keypad that corresponds to the layer you want activate, or press the <keycap>Delete</keycap> key for layer 10. You must perform this action within five seconds of the first action. If you do not press the layer number within five seconds, then <application>&app;</application> does  not change the current layer.</para></listitem></orderedlist> </para>

</sect2>
<sect2 id="gnopernicus-layer-modify"><title>To Modify Defined Layer Keys</title>
<para>Perform the following steps to modify layer keys that are already defined:</para>
	<orderedlist>
		<listitem>
			<para>Click on <guimenuitem>Command Mapping</guimenuitem> in the <application>&app;</application> menu window.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Open the <guilabel>Layers</guilabel> tab in the <guilabel>Command Mapping</guilabel> dialog.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Select the layer code you want to modify.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Click <guilabel>Modify</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Make your modifications.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Click <guilabel>OK</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</orderedlist>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="gnopernicus-keystrokes"><title>To Define Your Own Keystrokes</title>
<para>Perform the following steps to assign your own keystrokes to keys on your keyboard:</para>
	<orderedlist>
		<listitem>
			<para>Click on <guimenuitem>Command Mapping</guimenuitem> in the <application>&app;</application> menu window.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Open the <guilabel>User Defined</guilabel> tab in the <guilabel>Command Mapping</guilabel> dialog.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Click <guilabel>Add</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Create your keystroke sequence by selecting the modifier options.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Assign a key from your keyboard.
			</para>
		</listitem>
		<listitem>
			<para>Click <guilabel>OK</guilabel>
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</orderedlist>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="gnopernicus-speech-activate"><title>To Activate Speech Output</title><para>Speech output is normally active by default when <application>&app;</application> starts. However, if there is no speech output, click on  <guimenuitem>Startup Mode</guimenuitem> in the <application>&app;</application> menu window, then select the <guilabel>Speech</guilabel> option in the <guilabel>Startup Mode</guilabel> dialog.</para><para>Some useful assigned actions on the numeric keypad that you can use to work with the Speech output feature are as follows:
</para>
<para>
<informaltable frame="topbot"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colsep="0" rowsep="0" colwidth="1.00*"/><colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colsep="0" rowsep="0" colwidth="2.31*"/><thead><row rowsep="1" valign="top"><entry colname="col1" colsep="0" valign="top" rowsep="1"><para>Numeric Keypad Code</para></entry><entry colname="col2" colsep="0" valign="top"><para>Assigned Action</para></entry></row></thead><tbody><row valign="top"><entry colname="col1" colsep="0" rowsep="0" valign="top"><para>L08K13</para></entry><entry colname="col2" colsep="0" rowsep="0" valign="top"><para>Pause or continue reading a large chunk of text.</para></entry></row><row valign="top"><entry colname="col1" colsep="0" rowsep="0" valign="top"><para>L08K01</para></entry><entry colname="col2" colsep="0" rowsep="0" valign="top"><para>Decrease the speech volume.</para></entry></row><row valign="top"><entry colname="col1" colsep="0" rowsep="0" valign="top"><para>L00K05</para></entry><entry colname="col2" colsep="0" rowsep="0" valign="top"><para>Repeat last utterance. To spell out characters, press <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>Left Arrow</keycap></keycombo>.</para></entry></row><row><entry colname="col1" colsep="0" rowsep="0"><para>L03K04</para></entry><entry colname="col2" colsep="0" rowsep="0"><para>Provide speech output of the complete contents of a window through the heirarchy of the contents. This is called a <emphasis>logical review</emphasis>.</para></entry></row><row><entry colname="col1" colsep="0" rowsep="0"><para>L03K05</para></entry><entry colname="col2" colsep="0" rowsep="0"><para>Provide speech output of the complete contents of a window flattening the heirarchy in a left-to-right top-to-bottom way. This is called a <emphasis>spatial review</emphasis>.</para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></informaltable></para><para><?xm-replace_text {para}?></para></sect2>

<sect2 id="gnopernicus-brlmon-start"><title>To Start Braille Monitor</title><para>You can start Braille Monitor in the following ways:</para><variablelist>
		<varlistentry>
    		<term>&app; Menu Window</term>
    		<listitem>
    		<para>Open the Startup Mode dialog, then select the Braille Monitor option.</para>
    		</listitem>
    		</varlistentry>
    		<varlistentry>
    		<term>Command line</term>
    		<listitem>
    		<para>Execute the following command: <command>brlmonitor</command></para>
		<para>You  can specify the following options with the <command>brlmonitor</command> command: <informaltable frame="none"><tgroup cols="2" colsep="0" rowsep="0" align="left"><colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="1.00*" align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0"/><colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="1.82*" align="left" colsep="0" rowsep="0"/><tbody><row rowsep="0" valign="top"><entry colname="col1" align="left" rowsep="0" colsep="0" valign="top"><para>[-column | -c]</para></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top"><para>Number of columns on display </para></entry></row><row rowsep="0" valign="top"><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top"><para>[-line | -l]</para></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top"><para>Number of lines on display </para></entry></row><row rowsep="0" valign="top"><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top"><para>[-mode | -m] </para></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top"><para>Specifies the  font: [normal | braille | dual]</para></entry></row><row rowsep="0" valign="top"><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top"><para>[-port | -p] </para></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top"><para>UDP port number</para></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></informaltable>   </para>	
    		</listitem>
    		</varlistentry>
    		</variablelist>
	    </sect2>
<sect2 id="gnopernicus-braille-output"><title>To Activate Braille Output</title><para>Click on  <guimenuitem>Braille</guimenuitem> in the <application>&app;</application> menu window, then select the <guilabel>Braille</guilabel> option in the <guilabel>Startup Mode</guilabel> dialog.</para></sect2>

<sect2 id="gnopernicus-magnifier-activate"><title>To Activate the Magnifier</title>

<para>Click on  <guimenuitem>Magnifier</guimenuitem> in the <application>&app;</application> menu window, then select the <guilabel>Magnifier</guilabel> option in the <guilabel>Startup Mode</guilabel> dialog.</para>
<para>When the magnifier is activated, half of the screen appears normal size and the other half of the screen is magnified. The location of the cursor on the normal-size screen is indicated by a mobile crosshair on the magnified part of the screen.
</para>
</sect2>
</sect1>

