  <sect1 id="gnopernicus-preferences"> 
	 <title>Preferences</title> 
	 <para>
	 To control the behavior of the various functional areas in <application>&app;</application>, you  select options in preference dialogs specific to each functional area. To open the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> menu window, click on <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem> in the <guilabel>&app;</guilabel> menu window.
	 </para>
  <sect2 id="gnopernicus-speech-prefs"><title>Speech Preferences</title>
	<para>
	Click on <guilabel>Speech</guilabel> to open the <guilabel>Speech Preferences</guilabel> dialog.
	</para>
	<para>
	You can change the speech characteristics for punctuation reading, text echo, and several other parameters.
	</para>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="gnopernicus-braille-prefs"><title>Braille Preferences</title>
	<para>
	 	Click on <guilabel>Braille</guilabel> to open the <guilabel>Braille  Preferences</guilabel> dialog.
	</para>
	<para>
	You can change the following functionality: 

	</para>		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para>Braille device
				</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Translation table
				</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Braille style
				</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Cursor preferences
				</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Braille key mapping
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
</sect2>

